column1: Significant zonated pairs  (Kruskal Wallis q<0.2, mean expression>5E-6 UMI with score lower than -0.14, the 10 percentile obtained when randomizing enzyme identities). P-S are pairs in which the product of Enzyme 1 is the substrate of Enzyme2, S-S are pairs that utilize the same substrate, P-P are pairs that produce the same product, P-X-S denote triplets with an intermediate enzyme between Enzyme 1 and Enzyme 2.
